# Domain Layer

Pure, framework-free Dart. Keep it trivially unit-testable.

- No `package:flutter`, `package:drift`, or Riverpod imports here.
- Calculators are stateless static methods or immutable value objects
  (`NetWorthCalculator`, `LinearForecast`, `CurrencyConverter`).
- Currency math goes through `CurrencyConverter`; never multiply raw rates ad hoc.

```dart
// GOOD
final cny = converter.convert(amount: usd, from: Currency.usd, to: Currency.cny);

// BAD: bypasses the rate matrix
final cny = usd * 7.25;
```

- FX fallback numbers live in `fx_defaults.dart` (`kDefaultUsdToCny`,
  `kDefaultUsdToSgd`). Do not re-hardcode `7.25` / `1.35` anywhere.
- Enums in `models/enums.dart` own their own `label(l10n)` / `fromString`
  helpers; extend those rather than scattering `switch` statements.
